==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pandemonium
<hw>Pan`de*mo"ni*um</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., from Gr.
<grk>pa^s</grk>, <grk>pa^n</grk>, all + <grk>dai`mwn</grk> a
demon.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The great hall or council chamber of
demons or evil spirits.</def> <rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>An utterly lawless, riotous place or
assemblage.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A condition of unrestrained disorder and chaotic,
riotous uproar.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pander</ent>⟦br⟧
